basics.name: Felix Packard
basics.label: Software Engineer
basics.summary: I come from a land down under. I have over 5 years of professional experience, and I've been passionate about programming since the age of 12. Before starting rigr.gg, I worked for Passle as a full stack solutions architect. I'm a quick learner, perfectionist, and stalwart defender of the Oxford comma. When I'm not shipping products you'll find me playing piano or video games.

work.name: 🎮 rigr.gg
work.description: Showcase your PC setup and find inspiration from the community
work.summary: As the sole designer & developer, I designed and built the platform from scratch using Figma, Laravel, React, Inertia.js, and Tailwind CSS. The platform is hosted on AWS using a serverless architecture powered by Lambda, API Gateway, and S3.
highlights: Interactive experiences should feel like magic – the entire platform is built with a keen attention to detail and a focus on user experience

Avoiding technical debt – the platform is built with a focus on maintainability and scalability, with a consistent codebase, automated testing, CI/CD pipelines, robust error monitoring, and avoidance of unnecessary dependencies
Emphasis on performance – all queries, images, and assets are optimized for fast loading times

While marketing is in the early stages, we've already built a community of over 100 PC setup enthusiasts. We've onboarded several large Instagram creators who are using rigr.gg as their link in bio, and we're in talks with a company valued at over $150M about potential collaborations

work.name: 🐙 Passle
work.description: Content marketing platform for industry experts
work.summary: After doing freelance frontend development work for Passle, I was hired full-time to work on their .NET backend and Angular frontend as a junior developer, and quickly climbed the ranks to solutions architect.
highlights: Led strategy & development on Passle's enterprise offering, allowing clients to use Passle as a headless CMS via API endpoints and first party plugins for WordPress and Umbraco
Removed the need for a dedicated mobile team by instigating and leading a complete redesign and rebuild of the legacy Passle mobile app in React Native
Conducted technical interviews, trained, and managed additional developers as the team grew
Vastly improved results of stock image recommendation algorithm by introducing the use of LLMs
Built a consistent framework for AWS Lambda microservices, with automated unit testing, builds, and deployments via GitHub Actions
Built a proof-of-concept customer support chatbot using GPT-3 before there were any off-the-shelf solutions available
Rebuilt the custom design tool to make it easier for clients to use themselves, reducing the need to pay freelancers for design work

work.name: 🖥️ Felix IT
work.description: Self-employed IT support and web development
work.summary: Felix IT provided IT support and web development services, both on-site for local businesses, and remote for companies in the UK and Australia.
highlights: Designed and developed websites for small businesses
Diagnosed and fixed PC software and hardware issues

education.studyType: General education with a focus on computer science. I've been passionate about programming since the age of 12.
